Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F4-day-workweek-evidence-prevent-burnout-productivity-ai-well-being-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efour-day%20workweek%20reduces%20staff%20turnover%2C%20improves%20employee%20mental%20health%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20saves%20money%2C%20according%20to%20the%20largest%20public%20sector%20trial%20held%20in%20the%20UK.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20academics%20at%20two%20British%20universities%20%E2%80%94%20Cambridge%20and%20Salford%20%E2%80%94%20released%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscambs.moderngov.co.uk%2Fdocuments%2Fg9810%2FPublic%2520reports%2520pack%2520Monday%252015-Jul-2024%252010.30%2520Employment%2520and%2520Staffing%2520Committee.pdf%3FT%3D10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etheir%20findings%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20a%2015-month%20trial%20of%20a%20shortened%20working%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20experiment%2C%20which%20started%20in%20January%202023%2C%20was%20introduced%20by%20South%20Cambridgeshire%20District%20Council%20in%20southeast%20England.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20the%20largest%20public%20sector%20trial%20of%20the%20four-day%20workweek%20held%20so%20far%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20involving%20697%20employees%2C%20including%20office%20and%20waste%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20the%20project%2C%20people%20were%20expected%20to%20complete%20100%25%20of%20their%20work%20in%2080%25%20of%20the%20time%20for%20full%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20assessed%2024%20areas%2C%20such%20as%20worker%20motivation%2C%20staff%20mental%20health%2C%20and%20workers'%20commitment%20to%20their%20roles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOut%20of%20the%2024%20areas%20assessed%2C%20performance%20improved%20or%20stayed%20the%20same%20in%20a%20total%20of%2022.%20Staff%20turnover%20was%20reduced%20by%2039%25%2C%20significantly%20lowering%20recruitment%20demand.%20The%20number%20of%20external%20applicants%20for%20open%20roles%20also%20greatly%20increased%2C%20with%2076%25%20reporting%20the%20four-day%20week%20trial%20as%20influencing%20them%20to%20apply%20for%20open%20positions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProf%20Daiga%20Kamer%C4%81de%2C%20one%20of%20the%20report's%20authors%20and%20a%20professor%20of%20work%20and%20wellbeing%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Salford%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%3A%20%26quot%3BOrganizations%20that%20will%20be%20too%20reluctant%20to%20introduce%20the%20four-day%20week%20might%20start%20falling%20behind%2C%20because%20that's%20what%20we%20see%20in%20other%20trials%20already.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOrganizations%20who%20are%20forerunners%20in%20the%20industry%20of%20four-day%20workweek%20trials%20attract%20the%20best%20talent%20around%20because%20people%20say%20if%20I%20can%20do%20four%20days%20a%20week%20or%20five%20days%20a%20week%2C%20I'm%20going%20to%20go%20where%20I%20can%20do%20four%20days%20a%20week%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20project%20helped%20the%20council%20to%20save%20%C2%A3371%2C500%20(%24476%2C980)%2C%20mainly%20from%20agency%20staff%20costs%2C%20which%20related%20to%20only%2010%20posts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorkers%20saw%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-four-day-workweek-helps-workers-employers-science-evidence-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emental%20and%20physical%20health%20improve%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20their%20motivation%20levels%20rise%2C%20researchers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20see%20across%20the%20board%2C%20that%20if%20anything%2C%20there's%20a%20lot%20more%20evidence%20that%20things%20improved%20during%20the%20period%20of%20the%20trial%20compared%20to%20before%20the%20trial%2C%26quot%3B%20Prof%20Brendan%20Burchell%2C%20another%20author%20of%20the%20report%20and%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20faculty%20of%20Human%2C%20Social%20and%20Political%20Sciences%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Cambridge%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDiscussing%20the%20positive%20outcomes%20of%20the%20four-day%20workweek%20experiment%2C%20he%20said%3A%20%