as%20shocked%20by%20how%20much%20she%20loved%20living%20in%20the%20lesser-known%20English%20city.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Tanushree%20Srivastava)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-to-england-nottingham-surprising-things-2024-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Not%20In%20Open%20Court%3A%20Chief%20Justice%20On%20Review%20Petition%20In%20Same-Sex%20Marriage%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Tuesday%20did%20not%20agree%20to%20give%20an%20open%20court%20hearing%20on%20the%20review%20petition%20challenging%20the%20top%20court%20judgement%20that%20refused%20to%20legally%20recognise%20same-sex%20and%20queer%20marriage.%3Cbr%3E%5CnA%20bench%20headed%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20DY%20Chandrachud%20said%20that%20the%20constitution%20bench%20review%20is%20heard%20not%20in%20the%20open%20court%20but%20in%20chambers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20court's%20clarification%20came%20when%20petitioners%20mentioned%20the%20review%20petition%20challenging%20the%20same-sex%20marriage%20judgement%20dated%20October%2017%2C%202023%2C%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20urged%20for%20an%20open%20court%20hearing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20review%20petition%20was%20mentioned%20by%20senior%20Advocate%20NK%20Kaul%20urging%20the%20top%20court%20for%20an%20open%20hearing%20on%20a%20plea%20seeking%20legal%20recognition%20of%20same-sex%20and%20queer%20marriage%20under%20the%20Special%20Marriage%20Act%20(SMA)%2C%201954%2C%20Foreign%20Marriage%20Act%20(FMA)%2C%201969%2C%20Citizenship%20Act%2C%201955%2C%20the%20common%20law%20and%20other%20existing%20legislations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20will%20hear%20the%20review%20petition%20on%20July%2010.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20five-judge%20bench%20headed%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20DY%20Chandrachud%20will%20hear%20the%20petition.%20The%20other%20four%20judges%20on%20the%20bench%20are%20justices%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%2C%20Hima%20Kohli%2C%20BV%20Nagarathna%20and%20PS%20Narasimha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustices%20SK%20Kaul%20and%20S%20Ravindra%20Bhat%2C%20who%20have%20retired%20from%20the%20bench%20have%20been%20replaced%20by%20Justices%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%20and%20BV%20Nagarathna.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVarious%20review%20petitions%20have%20been%20filed%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20challenging%20the%20top%20court%20judgement%20which%20declined%20marriage%20equality%20right%20to%20queer%20couples.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20review%20petitions%20has%20been%20filed%20through%20advocates%20Karuna%20Nundy%20and%20Ruchira%20Goel%20which%20sought%20to%20review%20the%20majority%20judgment%20dated%20October%2017%2C%202023%2C%20passed%20by%20the%20top%20court%2C%20which%20rejected%20a%20batch%20of%20petitions%2C%20seeking%20legal%20recognition%20of%20same-sex%20and%20queer%20marriage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20court%20delivered%20four%20separate%20judgments%20dated%20October%2017%2C%202023.%20The%20majority%20judgement%20was%20delivered%20by%20justices%20SR%20Bhat%2C%20Hima%20Kohli%20and%20PS%20Narasimha.%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20DY%20Chandrachud%20and%20Justice%20SK%20Kaul%20have%20delivered%20minority%20judgements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20majority%20Judgement%20held%20that%20there%20is%20no%20fundamental%20right%20to%20marry%3B%20transgender%20persons%20have%20the%20right%20to%20heterosexual%20marriage%20under%20the%20existing%20provisions%20of%20the%20Transgender%20Persons%20(Protection%20of%20Rights)%20Act%2C%202019%20and%20the%20Transgender%20Persons%20(Protection%20of%20Rights)%20Rules%2C%202020%3B%20entitlement%20to%20legal%20recognition%20of%20the%20right%20to%20union%20-%20akin%20to%20marriage%20or%20civil%20union%2C%20or%20conferring%20legal%20status%20upon%20the%20parties%20to%20the%20relationship%20can%20be%20only%20through%20enacted%20law%20and%20the%20court%20cannot%20enjoin%20or%20direct%20the%20creation%20of%20such%20regulatory%20framework%20resulting%20in%20legal%20status.%20The%20majority%20judgement%20also%20denied%20giving%20any%20adoption%20right%20to%20queer%20couples%20as%20it%20held%20that%20Regulation%205(3)%20of%20the%20CARA%20Regulations%20cannot%20be%20held%20void.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20petitioners%20sought%20to%20review%20the%20Majority%20Judgment%20stating%20that%20it%20suffers%20from%20errors%20of%20law%2C%20application%20of%20law%20contrary%20to%20established%20principles%2C%20and%20commits%20a%20grave%20miscarriage%20of%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Majority%20Judgement%20erroneously%20holds%20that%20the%20issue%20of%20'whether%20the%20absence%20of%20law%20or%20a%20regulatory%20framework%2C%20or%20the%20failure%20of%20the%20State%20to%20enact%20law%2C%20amounts%20to%20discrimination%20that%20is%20protected%20against%20under%20Article%2015'%20was%20not%20argued%20or%20urged%20by%20the%20petitioners%2C%26quot%3B%20read%20the%20petition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Majority%20Judgement%20has%20erroneously%20failed%20to%20consider%20that%20the%20petitioner's%20prayers%20do%20not%20seek%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20new%20institution%20of%20marriage%20for%20the%20petitioners%2C%20but%20only%20to%20extend%20the%20existing%20legal%20institution%20of%20marriage%20and%20consequent%20benefits%20to%20the%20Petitioners.%20However%2C%20this%20is%20re-framing%20the%20right%20sought%20by%20the%20petitioners%20as%20a%20right%20to%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20new%20institution%2C%20which%20was%20not%20sought%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20petition%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Majority%20Judgment%20erroneously%20refuses%20to%20find%20Regulation%205(3)%20of%20the%20Adoption%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERegulations%2C%202022%20is%20unconstitutional%2C%20finding%20that%20the%20law%20treats%20children%20of%20married%20couples%20and%20unmarried%20couples%20differently.%20However%2C%20this%20is%20contrary%20to%20established%20principles%20of%20law%20because%2C%20as%20noted%20by%20Chandrachud%2C%20CJ.%20in%20his%20dissenting%20opinion%2C%20the%20law%20offers%20no%20protection%20to%20a%20child%20adopted%20by%20a%20married%20couple%2C%20that%20it%20does%20not%20offer%20to%20a%20child%20adopted%20by%20an%20unmarried%20couple%2C%26quot%3B%20read%20the%20plea.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20petition%20said%20that%20the%20operation%20of%20the%20Majority%20Judgement%20has%20grave%20consequences%20for%20the%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Elives%20and%20relationships%20that%20the%20petitioners%20have%20built%20together%20which%20remains%20outside%20the%20protection%20of%20the%20law.%20The%20dangers%20of%20the%20discrimination%20that%20has%20been%20recognised%20in%20all%20four%20opinions%20in%20the%20impugned%20judgments%20are%20the%20reality%20of%20the%20petitioners%20until%20they%20are%20recognised%20to%20be%20equal%20and%20on%20par%20with%20heterosexual%20couples%2C%20the%20petition%20further%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIndeed%2C%20the%20petitioners%20in%20the%20captioned%20petitions%20also%20have%20children%20who%20are%20also%20without%20this%20equal%20recognition%20of%20their%20family.%20On%20this%20basis%2C%20the%20errors%20in%20the%20Majority%20Judgment%20constitute%20a%20sweeping%20miscarriage%20of%20justice%2C%20warranting%20urgent%20scrutiny%20by%20the%20top%20court%20in%20the%20exercise%20of%20its%20review%20powers%26quot%3B%20the%20petition%20urged.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%20seeking%20to%20set%20aside%20earlier%20top%20court's%20order%2C%20the%20petition%20sought%20to%20consider%20the%20remedies%20under%2C%20Sections%2015-18%20of%20the%20Special%20Marriage%20Act%2C%201954.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20petition%20said%20that%20reading%20the%20provisions%20under%20Sections%2015-18%20for%20the%20solemnization%20of%20%26quot%3Bmarriages%20celebrated%20in%20other%20forms%26quot%3B%20to%20be%20made%20available%20for%20non-heterosexual%20marriages%2C%20which%20may%20-%20in%20turn%20-%20be%20permitted%20to%20evolve%20through%20common%20law%20prevents%20an%20exercise%20of%20%26quot%3Breading%20in%2Fdown%26quot%3B%20any%20provision%20of%20the%20SMA%20and%20gives%20effect%20to%20the%20top%20court's%20recognition%20of%20the%20constitutional%20rights%20of%20non-heterosexual%20and%20queer%20marriages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720521960000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-07%2Fdbuvihn_supreme-court-istock_625x300_02_July_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fnot-in-open-court-chief-justice-on-review-petition-in-same-sex-marriage-6067408%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Tuesday%20did%20not%20agree%20to%20give%20an%20open%20court%20hearing%20on%20the%20review%20petition%20challenging%20the%20top%20court%20judgement%20that%20refused%20to%20legally%20recognise%20same-sex%20and%20queer%20marriage.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fnot-in-open-court-chief-justice-on-review-petition-in-same-sex-marriage-6067408%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fnot-in-open-court-chief-justice-on-review-petition-in-same-sex-marriage-6067408%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fnot-in-open-court-chief-justice-on-review-petition-in-same-sex-marriage-6067408%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Beware%2C%20Elon%20Musk%20%E2%80%94%20BYD%20just%20took%20its%20next%20step%20toward%20world%20domination%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22789%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22BYD%20CEO%20Wang%20Chuanfu%20signs%20deal%20for%20new%20factory%20with%20Turkish%20President%20Recep%20Erdo%C4%9Fan%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com