gure%20had%20fallen%20to%20about%2089%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20several%20explanations%20for%20this%20trend%20is%20that%20in%20recent%20decades%2C%20it's%20become%20difficult%20for%20some%20men%20to%20land%20a%20well-paying%20job%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-openings-bachelors-college-degree-no-education-requirements-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewithout%20a%20college%20degree%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20development%20that's%20contributed%20to%20some%20men%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Fmen-not-at-work-why-so-many-men-ages-of-25-to-54-are-not-working%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eleaving%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20labor%20force.%20These%20challenges%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcollege-degree-good-job-market-skill-based-hiring-employers-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epersist%20today%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20men%20even%20as%20more%20companies%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-ibm-accenture-dell-companies-no-longer-require-college-degrees-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estarted%20hiring%20candidates%3C%2Fa%3E%20without%20a%20degree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20perceived%20benefits%20of%20a%20college%20degree%20have%20led%20more%20Americans%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-going-back-to-school-college-degree-career-advancement-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ego%20back%20to%20school%20%3C%2Fa%3Elater%20in%20life.%20About%2034%25%20of%20college%20undergraduates%20and%2044%25%20of%20community%20college%20enrollees%20are%20age%2025%20or%20older%2C%20according%20to%20the%20National%20Center%20for%20Education%20Statistics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20Ferraro%20and%20many%20recent%20college%20graduates%20can%20attest%20to%2C%20having%20a%20degree%20doesn't%20guarantee%20success%20in%20the%20job%20market.%20Last%20November%2C%20the%20un