perfect%26quot%3B%20job%20for%20him%20to%20kick-start%20his%20new%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20early%20stages%20of%20the%20interview%20process%20seemed%20promising%2C%20but%20he%20said%20things%20changed%20when%20he%20had%20an%20in-person%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20soon%20as%20the%20hiring%20manager%20saw%20me%2C%20his%20whole%20demeanor%20changed%2C%26quot%3B%20Ferraro%20said.%20%26quot%3BHe%20ran%20through%20the%20questions%20and%20never%20truly%20engaged%20with%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20weeks%20later%2C%20Ferraro%20learned%20that%20he%20was%20no%20longer%20being%20considered%20for%20the%20role.%20The%20only%20explanation%20that%20made%20sense%20to%20him%20was%20that%20the%20hiring%20manager%20wasn't%20interested%20in%20candidates%20as%20old%20as%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20man%20in%20his%20forties%2C%20who%20is%20the%20perfect%20candidate%20on%20paper%2C%20willing%20to%20work%2C%20willing%20to%20learn%2C%20and%20willing%20to%20apply%20himself%20to%20any%20task%2C%20is%20still%20a%20man%20in%20his%2040s%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BTherefore%2C%20not%20a%20valid%20candidate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFerraro%20needed%20an%20income%2C%20and%20after%20struggling%20to%20land%20jobs%20in%20his%20field%20of%20study%2C%20he%20reluctantly%20decided%20to%20expand%20his%20search%20to%20the%20truck%20driver%20jobs%20he'd%20hoped%20to%20escape.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20despite%20his%20decades%20of%20prior%20experience%2C%20Ferraro%20said%20he%20struggled%20to%20land%20an%20interview%20for%20driving%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20a%20development%20that%20baffled%20him.%20But%20then%20he%20had%20an%20idea%3A%20What%20if%20he%20removed%20his%20college%20education%20from%20his%20r%C3%A9sume%20when%20he%20applied%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20did%20not%20start%20receiving%20interviews%20until%20I%20removed%20the%20education%20section%20on%20my%20application%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BMy%20degree%20was%20holding%20me%20back.%2