%20had%20paid%20for%20my%20seat%2C%20how%20many%20miles%20I%20had%20used%20for%20the%20indulgence%20of%20an%20upgrade.%20But%20I%20had%20no%20idea%20if%20the%20woman%20across%20the%20aisle%20had%20spent%20only%20a%20few%20points%2C%20as%20I%20had%2C%20or%20paid%20the%20more%20than%20%2410%2C000%20the%20airline%20could%20charge%20for%20the%20same%20trip.%20To%20book%20a%20flight%20has%20long%20been%20to%20play%20a%20game%20where%20only%20the%20airline%20knows%20the%20rules%2C%20with%20countless%20booking%20codes%2C%20loyalty%20programs%2C%20and%20fare%20changes%20that%20weaponize%20your%20data%20against%20your%20wallet.%20But%20after%20I%20landed%2C%20I%20kept%20seeing%20the%20same%20rigged%20game%20everywhere%3A%20in%20every%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-lyft-driving-worth-it-strategies-tips-clean-car-talking-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUber%3C%2Fa%3E%20ride%2C%20every%20Amazon%20order%2C%20every%20trip%20to%20the%20supermarket.%20All%20these%20businesses%20now%20know%20so%20much%20about%20me%20that%20they%20can%20see%20a%20number%20blinking%20above%20my%20head%3A%20the%20exact%20price%20I'd%20be%20willing%20to%20pay%20in%20a%20given%20moment.%20Your%20own%20number%20is%20blinking%20above%20your%20head%20right%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20algorithmic%20age%2C%20pricing%20variability%20is%20increasingly%20creeping%20into%20digital%20commerce%2C%20with%20charges%20going%20up%20and%20down%20in%20real%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20far%20more%20disturbing%20is%20the%20rise%20of%20personalized%20pricing%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretail%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edigital%20retailers'%3C%2Fa%3E%20practice%20of%20exploiting%20your%20own%20data%20to%20charge%20the%20precise%20price%20you're%20willing%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcredit-card-disputes-friendly-fraud-perks-chargebacks-purchases-reviews-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epay%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20might%20be%20different%20from%20what%20the%20guy%20next%20to%20you%20would%20pay.%20Personalized%20pricing%20not%20only%20bakes%20in%20bias%20and%20can%20drive%20inflation%20but%20creates%20a%20world%20where%20you%20never%20know%20when%20your%20apps%20are%20ripping%20you%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20when%20I'm%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20paying%20for%20anything%20on%20my%20phone%20or%20laptop%2C%20I%20second-guess%20whether%20I'd%20be%20paying%20less%20if%20I%20were%20using%20someone%20else's%20account.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EI%20still%20remember%20the%20low-grade%20shock%20I%20felt%20a%20decade%20ago%20when%20I%20learned%20that%20price%20discrimination%20is%20often%20perfectly%20legal%20in%20the%20United%20States.%20In%20law%20school%2C%20my%20antitrust%20professor%20introduced%20us%20to%20the%20obscure%20Depression-era%20Robinson-Patman%20Antidiscrimination%20Act%20by%20quickly%20highlighting%20that%20this%20law%20very%20much%20failed%20to%20live%20up%20to%20its%20title.%20Under%20the%20long-standing%20law%2C%20companies%20can%20face%20ruinous%20penalties%20for%20price%20discrimination%20only%20if%20they're%20discriminating%20against%20other%20businesses.%20If%20a%20wholesaler%20overcharged%20a%20store%2C%20the%20store%20could%20take%20it%20to%20court%2C%20but%20there%20was%20nothing%20then%20(or%20now)%20to%20stop%20the%20store%20from%20doing%20the%20same%20thing%20to%20its%20customers.%20That%20is%2C%20store%20owners%20have%20more%20price%20protections%20than%20their%20customers.%20If%20a%20store%20generally%20charges%20some%20customers%20more%20than%20others%20because%20of%20their%20gender%2C%20race%2C%20or%20other%20legally%20protected%20characteristics%2C%20that's%20certainly%20illegal.%20But%20when%20companies%20want%20to%20shake%20down%20each%20customer%20for%20the%20most%20they're%20individually%20willing%20to%20pay%2C%20they're%20free%20to%20engage%20in%20highway%20robbery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20phone%20showing%20analytics%20attached%20to%20a%20pixel%20price%20tag%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66884621268f62ba18a7d96f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEven%20in%20polarized%20times%2C%20AI%20pickpocketing%20may%20be%20one%20of%20those%20rare%20issues%20that%20can%20unite%20us%20in%20outrage.%3Cp%3ETyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20say%20low-grade%20shock%20because%20at%20the%20time%20personalized%20pricing%20discrimination%20was%20far%20less%20widespread%20and%20harmful%20than%20it%20is%20today.%20Sure%2C%20coupon%20culture%20let%20companies%20sell%20the%20same%20product%20in%20the%20same%20store%20at%20the%20same%20time%20at%20different%20prices%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20gave%20customers%20agency.%20Price-sensitive%20shoppers%20took%20the%20time%20to%20scour%20for%20clippings%2C%20and%20less%20thrifty%20ones%20paid%20full%20freight.%20Coupons%2C%20loyalty%20cards%2C%20seasonal%20discounts%20%E2%80%94%20a%20lot%20of%20traditional%20price%20discrimination%20lets%20individual%20shoppers%20choose%20which%20price%20group%20they%20want%20to%20fall%20into.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20algorithmic%20price%20discrimination%20takes%20away%20that%20choice.%20And%20the%20methods%20to%20extract%20data%20to%20sort%20people%20into%20pricing%20groups%20are%20more%20invasive%20than%20you%20may%20realize.%20Take%20your%20latest%20Uber%20trip.%20When%20you%20ordered%20that%20car%2C%20you%20probably%20knew%20that%20the%20distance%20you%20were%20going%20and%20the%20time%20of%20day%20were%20price%20factors%2C%20as%20we've%20grown%20begrudgingly%20accustomed%20to%20the%20cold%2C%20extractive%20efficiency%20of%20surge%20pricing.%20But%20did%20you%20think%20about%20plugging%20in%20your%20phone%20before%20ordering%20the%20ride%3F%20If%20you%20did%2C%20it%20might%20have%20saved%20you%20a%20few%20bucks%2C%20because%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2024-06-03%2Fcompanies-are-getting-smarter-about-raising-their-prices%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebattery%20level%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20allegedly%20one%20of%20the%20factors%20Uber%20uses%20to%20price%20your%20trip%2C%20a%20charge%20that%20Uber%20vigorously%20denies.%20If%20the%20allegations%20against%20Uber%20are%20true%2C%20it's%20easy%20to%20see%20a%20rationale%3A%20Those%20with%20less%20battery%20left%20are%20more%20desperate%2C%20and%20those%20whose%20phones%20are%20minutes%20away%20from%20dying%20won't%20hesitate%20to%20pay%20nearly%20any%20price%20to%20get%20a%20car%20before%20they're%20stranded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprospect.org%2Feconomy%2F2024-06-04-one-person-one-price%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20American%20Prospect%20recently%20detailed%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20this%20type%20of%20individualized%20pricing%20is%20proliferating%20across%20nearly%20every%20sector%20of%20the%20economy%20(streaming%2C%20fast%20food%2C%20and%20even%20dating%20apps)%2C%20and%20it%20can%20be%20surprising%20which%20variables%20will%20get%20you%20charged%20more.%20In%20the%202010s%2C%20retailers%20relied%20on%20somewhat%20crude%20data%20to%20perfect%20pricing.%20Customers%20might've%20paid%20more%20for%20a%20flight%20they%20booked%20on%20a%20Mac%20(versus%20a%20PC)%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.propublica.org%2Farticle%2Fasians-nearly-twice-as-likely-to-get-higher-price-from-princeton-review%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaid%20a%20higher%20rate%20for%20test%20prep%20in%20ZIP%20codes%20with%20larger%20Asian%20communities%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20in%20recent%20years%20companies%20have%20moved%20from%20neighborhood-level%20price%20discrimination%20to%20individualized%20pricing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERetailers%20like%20Amazon%20know%20so%2C%20so%20much%20about%20what%20you%20buy%2C%20both%20on%20its%20platform%20and%20off.%20And%20you%20have%20no%20way%20of%20knowing%20when%20your%20choices%20are%20changing%20what%20you%20pay.%20In%202018%2C%20it%20was%20headline%20news%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-price-changes-2018-8%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%20adjusted%20prices%202.5%20million%20times%20a%20day%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Given%20Amazon's%20growth%20and%20the%20growth%20of%20AI%2C%20the%20number%20is%20likely%20an%20order%20of%20magnitude%20higher%20today.%20For%20retailers%20like%20Walmart%2C%20it's%20not%20enough%20to%20use%20our%20shopping%20history.%20In%20February%2C%20the%20retail%20behemoth%20agreed%20to%20buy%20the%20smart-TV%20maker%20Vizio%20for%20more%20than%20%242%20billion%2C%20potentially%20giving%20Walmart%20a%20windfall%20of%20intimate%20consumer%20data.%20Smart%20TVs%20not%20only%20monitor%20what%20we%20watch%20with%20Orwellian%20precision%20but%20track%20other%20nearby%20devices%20with%20ultrasonic%20beacons%2C%20and%20can%20even%20listen%20in%20to%20what%20we%20say%20in%20the%20privacy%20of%20our%20own%20homes.%20Vizio%20specifically%20has%20been%20fined%20millions%20of%20dollars%20over%20allegations%20that%20it%20illegally%20spied%20on%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20do%20retailers%20know%20what%20you've%20bought%20and%20how%20much%20money%20you%20make%2C%20but%20often%20they%20know%20where%20you%20are%2C%20how%20your%20day%20is%20going%2C%20and%20what%20your%20mood%20is%20like%2C%20all%20of%20which%20can%20be%20neatly%20synthesized%20by%20AI%20neural%20networks%20to%20calculate%20how%20much%20you'd%20pay%20for%20a%20given%20item%20in%20a%20given%20moment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20area%20of%20commerce%20is%20too%20personal%20to%20be%20off-limits.%20Dating%20apps%20are%20harvesting%20our%20romantic%20lives%20for%20data%2C%20but%20some%20openly%20brag%20about%20doing%20so%20to%20increase%20profitability.%20And%20many%20of%20those%20that%20don't%20disclose%20using%20personalized%20pricing%20still%20do%20it.%20Tinder%20rarely%20talks%20about%20its%20pricing%20technology%2C%20but%20Mozilla%20and%20Consumers%20International%20recently%20found%20that%20the%20dating%20app%20used%20dozens%20of%20variables%20to%20radically%20adjust%20pricing%20for%20users.%20Your%20age%2C%20gender%2C%20and%20sexual%20orientation%20might%20determine%20what%20the%20AI%20decides%20you%20need%20to%20pay%20for%20love.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ELeft%20unchecked%2C%20personalized%20pricing%20will%20have%20pernicious%20effects%20across%20society.%20Nikolas%20Guggenberger%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Houston%20Law%20Center%2C%20says%20that%20%26quot%3Bhidden%20algorithmic%20price%20discrimination%20can%20undermine%20public%20trust%20in%20price-building%20mechanisms%20and%20thus%20undermine%20the%20marketplace.%26quot%3B%20AI%20pricing%20also%20means%20that%20those%20who%20are%20the%20most%20desperate%20and%20most%20vulnerable%20will%20often%20pay%20the%20most.%20Even%20worse%2C%20people%20could%20be%20penalized%20because%20of%20their%20race%2C%20age%2C%20or%20class.%20Take%20the%20phone-battery%20allegation.%20Older%20people%20are%20more%20than%20twice%20as%20likely%20than%20younger%20users%20to%20have%20a%20phone%20that's%20at%20least%20three%20years%20old.%20Since%20older%20smartphones%20tend%20to%20have%20lower%20battery%20life%2C%20older%20people%20could%20end%20up%20paying%20more%20than%20younger%20people%20for%20the%20same%20Uber%20rides.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlgorithmic%20price%20discrimination%20can%20basically%20automate%20usury%2C%26quot%3B%20Guggenberger%20says.%20%26quot%3BIf%20your%20battery%20is%20about%20to%20die%20and%20you%20are%20out%20in%20the%20country%2C%20a%20ride-sharing%20app%20may%20drastically%20raise%20your%20'personalized%20price.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20much%20of%20AI%20pricing%20acts%20as%20a%20regressive%20tax%2C%20charging%20those%20with%20the%20most%20the%20least.%20For%20people%20in%20underserved%20areas%2C%20with%20fewer%20stores%2C%20fewer%20alternatives%2C%20there's%20often%20no%20choice%20but%20to%20click%20%26quot%3Bbuy%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20even%20when%20it%20hurts.%20As%20the%20law%20professor%20and%20consumer%20watchdog%20Zephyr%20Teachout%20told%20The%20American%20Prospect%2C%20we%20shouldn't%20think%20of%20this%20practice%20as%20something%20as%20innocuous-sounding%20as%20personalized%20pricing%20%E2%80%94%20instead%2C%20she%20calls%20it%20surveillance%20pricing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20know%20how%20to%20prove%20human%20discrimination.%20If%20a%20store%20in%20a%20majority-Black%20neighborhood%20charges%20more%20than%20its%20counterpart%20in%20a%20majority-white%20neighborhood%2C%20testers%20can%20go%20to%20each%20store%2C%20record%20the%20prices%2C%20and%20bring%20a%20lawsuit.%20This%20sort%20of%20testing%20has%20been%20at%20the%20core%20of%20consumer%20protections%20for%20most%20of%20a%20century.%20But%20how%20do%20you%20prove%20when%20an%20algorithm%20discriminates%3F%20There%20are%20no%20stores%20to%20visit%2C%20no%20price%20tags%20to%20compare%2C%20just%20millions%20of%20screens%20siloed%20in%20people's%20pockets.%20The%20result%20can%20be%20a%20Catch-22%2C%20where%20you%20can%20get%20enough%20data%20to%20prove%20the%20discrimination%20only%20by%20suing%20a%20company%2C%20but%20you%20can't%20sue%20the%20company%20without%20first%20having%20the%20data.%20We%20could%20see%20the%20rise%20of%20a%20perverse%2C%20bizarro%20legal%20world%20where%20companies%20using%20bias-prone%20AI%20to%20adjust%20prices%20in%20secret%20face%20less%20legal%20scrutiny%20than%20brick-and-mortar%20stores.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20hope%20is%20that%20this%20situation%20is%20so%20bleak%2C%20the%20potential%20for%20abuse%20so%20clear%2C%20that%20not%20even%20our%20dysfunctional%20democracy%20will%20accept%20it.%20Our%20lawmakers%20have%20been%20so%20slow%20to%20rein%20in%20the%20harms%20of%20novel%20technology%2C%20even%20when%20it%20becomes%20clear%2C%20for%20example%2C%20that%20it's%20undermining%20our%20democracy.%20But%20even%20in%20these%20polarized%20times%2C%20AI%20pickpocketing%20may%20be%20one%20of%20those%20rare%20issues%20that%20can%20unite%20us%20in%20outrage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Falbert-fox-cahn%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAlbert%20Fox%20Cahn%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20the%20founder%20and%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20Surveillance%20Technology%20Oversight%20Project%2C%20or%20STOP%2C%20a%20New%20York-based%20civil-rights%20and%20privacy%20group.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-quietly-picking-your-pocket-with-personalized-pricing-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720518722000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6688457b268f62ba18a7d93e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-quietly-picking-your-pocket-with-personalized-pricing-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Retailers%20have%20figured%20out%20how%20to%20set%20prices%20based%20on%20your%20age%2C%20mood%2C%20and%20sexual%20orientation.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Albert%20Fox%20Cahn)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-quietly-picking-your-pocket-with-personalized-pricing-2024-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Jasprit%20Bumrah%2C%20Smriti%20Mandhana%20named%20as%20ICC%20players%20for%20June%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720518659000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-111604492%2Cimgsize-101758.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Fnews%2Fjasprit-bumrah-smriti-mandhana-named-as-icc-players-of-the-month-for-june%2Farticleshow%2F111604552.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22ICC%20honored%20I