%20of%20buyers%2C%20the%20e-commerce%20giants%20of%20China%20are%20increasingly%20using%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-618-win-shoppers-sales-down-consumer-spending-discretionary-luxury-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emassive%20discounts%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20woo%20customers%20to%20their%20sales.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-618-win-shoppers-sales-down-consumer-spending-discretionary-luxury-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFor%20example%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20Alibaba%20recently%20offered%20a%2050%25%20discount%20on%20Lululemon%20clothing%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FJD.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJD.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20sold%20Apple%20iPhones%20with%20discounts%20as%20high%20as%2020%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20platforms%20also%20hold%20multiple%20sales%20throughout%20the%20year%2C%20from%20the%20Lunar%20New%20Year%20to%20Christmas%2C%20instead%20of%20concentrating%20them%20all%20on%20Singles'%20Day%20or%20the%20618%20sale%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2279a20a4a-53fa-422a-be59-a355d318e173%5C%22%3EBut%20the%20Chinese%20are%20just%20spending%20less%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EChina's%20post-pandemic%20economy%20being%20slow%20to%20recover%20may%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-economy-weak-domestic-demand-factory-activity-amid-strong-export-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20to%20do%20with%20internal%2C%20rather%20than%20external%20factors.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20country%20has%20reported%20sluggish%20domestic%20demand%2C%20with%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.stats.gov.cn%2Fsj%2Fzxfb%2F202406%2Ft20240630_1955251.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eofficial%20Purchasing%20Managers'%20Index%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20which%20represents%20larger%20companies%20and%20state-owned%20enterprises%20%E2%80%94%20contracting%20for%20the%20second%20straight%20month%20in%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20reason%20for%20this%20is%20low%20consumer%20confidence%20and%20people%20being%20more%20discerning%20about%20their%20purchases%2C%20Allison%20Malmsten%2C%20a%20director%20at%20Daxue%20Consulting%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BConsumer%20confidence%20is%20lower%3B%20people%20are%20more%20selective%20on%20what%20they%20spend%20money%20on%20and%2C%20therefore%2C%20will%20buy%20things%20because%20they%20need%20them%2C%20not%20because%20of%20a%20flashy%20discount%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20an%20excess%20of%20sales%20all%20year%20round%2C%20these%20annual%20mega%20sales%20are%20also%20gradually%20losing%20their%20luster%2C%20according%20to%20Yaling%20Jiang%2C%20a%20China%20consumer%20research%20expert%20behind%20the%20newsletter%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chineseconsumers.news%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BFollowing%20the%20Yuan.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20excess%20of%20sales%20events%2C%20which%20caused%20marketing%20fatigue%2C%20isn't%20new%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20to%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20shift%20in%20consumer%20behavior%20is%20deeper%20than%20just%20marketing%20fatigue%2C%20as%20the%20Chinese%20are%20%26quot%3Bbecoming%20rational%2C%20increasingly%20focusing%20on%20cost-effectiveness%20and%20necessity%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222ae6f631-0754-4451-808b-778fd2dee3d7%5C%22%3EEconomic%20factors%20at%20play%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20if%20people%20are%20spending%20less%2C%20that's%20because%20they're%20also%20not%20making%20big%20bucks%20in%20China's%20post-pandemic%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20economic%20downturn%20is%20making%20them%20want%20to%20avoid%20paying%20premiums%20as%20much%20as%20possible%2C%20and%20uncertainty%20about%20the%20future%20makes%20them%20want%20to%20save%20for%20a%20rainy%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20China%20consumer%20expert%20Jiang%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3