or%20a%20working%20mom%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20in%20Finland%2C%20this%20is%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20decisions%20new%20American%20mothers%20make.%20Due%20to%20the%20work%20culture%20in%20the%20US%2C%20choosing%20%3Cspan%3Ea%3C%2Fspan%3E%20career%20requires%20giving%20up%20most%20of%20the%20time%20with%20your%20child%2C%20and%20staying%20at%20home%20requires%20giving%20up%20work%20interests.%20In%20Finland%2C%20most%20women%20return%20back%20to%20work%2C%20as%20it%20doesn't%20require%20giving%20up%20too%20much%20family%20time%20with%20the%2037.5-hour%20workweek%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpost-pandemic-travel-vacation-micro-trips-2021-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elong%20vacations%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20option%20for%20part-time%20schedules.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20understood%20I%20couldn't%20find%20that%20in%20the%20US%2C%20but%20I%20hadn't%20realized%20I%20would%20have%20to%20give%20up%20so%20much%20more%20than%20time%20with%20my%20kids%20just%20to%20return%20to%20work%20%E2%80%94%20I%20had%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchildcare-too-expensive-unaffordable-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egive%20up%20most%20of%20my%20salary%3C%2Fa%3E.%20After%20we%20had%20had%20two%20kids%2C%20I%20was%20offered%20an%20exciting%20new%20job%20opportunity%20with%20fantastic%20pay.%20Yet%2C%20after%20I%20calculated%20the%20cost%20of%20two%20kids%20in%20nursery%20school%20along%20with%20a%20full%20time%20nanny%2C%20there%20was%20nothing%20much%20left%20%E2%80%94%20except%20my%20husband's%20salary%20%E2%80%94%20to%20live%20on.%20I%20still%20almost%20took%20the%20job%2C%20but%20in%20benefits%20negotiations%2C%20I%20was%20told%20there%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bno%20flexibility.%26quot%3B%20That%20was%20it%20for%20me.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222dcd516a-920b-4a6a-bd76-bd0523a46140%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAmerican%20parents%20do%20a%20lot%20for%20their%20kids%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAmerican%20parents%20around%20me%20tend%20to%20care%20for%20their%20children%20by%20doing%20a%20lot%20for%20them%20and%20by%20removing%20discomforts%20and%20obstacles%2C%20while%20in%20the%20Nordics%2C%20parents%20show%20care%20by%20both%20letting%20and%20pushing%20their%20kids%20to%20do%20what%20they%20are%20capable%20of%20to%20prepare%20them%20for%20the%20world.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20have%20accidentally%20baffled%20many%20American%20parents%20by%20raising%20my%20children%20like%20kids%20are%20raised%20in%20the%20Nordics%2C%20embracing%20all%20types%20of%20weather%20and%20encouraging%20them%20to%20be%20independent.%20We%20live%20within%20walking%20distance%20of%20their%20school%2C%20so%2C%20wearing%20the%20appropriate%20gear%2C%20we%20walk%20in%20rain%2C%20shine%2C%20snow%2C%20or%20sleet.%20I%20have%20let%20my%20boys%20race%20well%20past%20me%20on%20scooters%2C%20even%20as%20toddlers%2C%20and%20run%20around%20playgrounds%20as%20I%20sit%20on%20the%20sidelines.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftips-from-elementary-teacher-how-to-prepare-kids-for-school-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eelementary%20age%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20I%20have%20them%20schedule%20their%20playdates%20so%20they%20call%20their%20friends'%20parents%20to%20organize%20them.%20And%2C%20after%20school%2C%20I%20suggest%20they%20skip%20homework%20to%20get%20that%20essential%20playtime%20outside%20after%20school%20instead%20(the%20American%20school%20day%20is%20two%20to%20three%20hours%20longer%20than%20the%20Finnish%20one%2C%20with%20less%20recess).%20And%2C%20if%20our%20elementary-age%20children%20don't%20want%20to%20join%20us%20when%20we%20run%20errands%2C%20we%20welcome%20them%20to%20stay%20home%20%E2%80%94%20alone.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThey%20thrive%20with%20autonomy%2C%20and%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20do%2C%20too.%20However%2C%20finding%20opportunities%20for%20them%20to%20develop%20their%20independence%20is%20a%20challenge%3A%20I%20often%20get%20asked%20if%20my%20kids%20are%20indeed%20mine%20when%20I'm%20only%20a%20short%20distance%20away%20or%20asked%20to%20supervise%20them%2C%20even%20if%20I%20can%20see%20them%20but%20not%20hover%20over%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22adb0684d-cc67-4fb6-b8f8-d42a01eb27be%5C%22%3EI%20do%20less%20parenting%20in%20Finland%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBack%20in%20the%20US%2C%20I%20have%20decided%20to%20consciously%20create%20more%20bandwidth%20by%20opting%20out%20of%20many%20voluntary%20but%20culturally%20encouraged%20American%20mom%20tasks%2C%20from%20participation%20in%20school%20activities%20during%20the%20daytime%20to%20scheduling%20%E2%80%94%20and%20attending%20%E2%80%94%20countless%20travel%20sports%20and%20choosing%20simpler%20commitments%20instead.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20don't%20spend%20much%20time%20entertaining%20my%20kids%2C%20allowing%20them%20to%20take%20the%20lead%20in%20creating%20their%20own%20fun.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20I%20help%20my%20kids%20master%20independence%20skills%2C%20like%20the%20autonomous%20morning%20routine%2C%20so%20I%20can%20drink%20my%20coffee%20hot%2C%20workout%2C%20and%20get%20ready%20%E2%80%94%20while%20they%20get%20themselves%20ready.%20And%2C%20to%20balance%20the%20load%20of%20the%20invisible%20work%2C%20I%20have%20outsourced%20things%20that%20can't%20not%20be%20done%20to%20my%20husband%2C%20such%20as%20school%20registrations%20and%20passport%20renewals%20because%20they%20have%20motivating%20natural%20consequences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20came%20to%20the%20US%20for%20the%20American%20dream%20but%20found%20something%20else%20that%20led%20me%20to%20thrive%3A%20Nordic%20principles%20of%20balance%2C%20bandwidth%2C%20and%20autonomy%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20innovative%20spirit%20of%20American%20moms.%20In%20the%20US%2C%20I%20see%20massive%20amounts%20of%20brilliance%20hiding%20in%20plain%20sight%3A%20well-educated%20career%20women%20who%20are%20not%20able%20to%20use%20their%20talents%20because%2C%20after%20kids%2C%20it's%20simply%20too%20exhausting%20on%20all%20levels.%20So%20they%20decide%20to%20work%20outside%20the%20system%2C%20and%20completely%20reinvent%20themselves%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20so%20did%20I.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffinnish-mom-in-the-us-shares-differences-in-parenting-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720513383000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F668c04b1098114dafd1a4b10%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffinnish-mom-in-the-us-shares-differences-in-parenting-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22I've%20been%20in%20the%20US%20for%20decades%20and%20have%20three%20children.%20I%20let%20my%20kids%20schedule%20their%20own%20playdates%20and%20encourage%20indepence.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Annabella%20Daily)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffinnish-mom-in-the-us-shares-differences-in-parenting-2024-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Most%20Cancer%20Patients%20Die%20Of%20%26quot%3BCachexia%26quot%3B%2C%20Not%20Cancer%3A%20Read%20Details%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWhen%20tumours%20in%20cancer%20patients%20elevate%20levels%20of%20an%20immune%20system%20molecule%20called%20Interleukin-6%20(IL-6)%2C%20it%20can%20cause%20severe%20brain%20dysfunction%2C%20which%20leads%20to%20a%20lethal%20wasting%20disease%20called%20'cachexia'%20in%20about%2050%20to%2080%20per%20cent%20of%20cancer%20patients%2C%20a%20new%20study%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20US-based%20Cold%20Spring%20Harbor%20Laboratory's%20(CSHL)%20Professor%20Bo%20Li%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20very%20severe%20syndrome%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20people%20with%20cancer%20die%20of%20'cachexia'%20instead%20of%20cancer.%20And%20once%20the%20patient%20enters%20this%20stage%2C%20there's%20no%20way%20to%20go%20back%20because%20essentially%20there's%20no%20treatment%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20a%20study%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20Nature%20Communications.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELi%20and%20other%20researchers%20in%20the%20team%20found%20that%20blocking%20'IL-6'%20from%20binding%20to%20neurons%20in%20a%20part%20of%20the%20brain%20called%20the%20area%20postrema%20(AP)%20prevents%20cachexia%20in%20mice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20the%20mice%20live%20longer%20with%20healthier%20brain%20function.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFuture%20drugs%20targeting%20these%20neurons%20could%20help%20make%20cancer%20cachexia%20a%20treatable%20disease%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20suggested.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20healthy%20patients%2C%20'IL-6'%20plays%20a%20vital%20role%20in%20natural%20immune%20response.%20The%20molecules%20circulate%20throughout%20the%20body.%20When%20they%20encounter%20a%20possible%20threat%2C%20they%20alert%20the%20brain%20to%20coordinate%20a%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20researchers%2C%20cancer%20disrupts%20this%20process%20as%20too%20much%20IL-6%20gets%20produced%2C%20and%20it%20begins%20binding%20to%20AP%20neurons%20in%20the%20brain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20leads%20to%20several%20consequences.%20One%20is%20animals%20and%20humans%20alike%20will%20stop%20eating.%20Another%20is%20to%20engage%20this%20response%20that%20leads%20to%20the%20wasting%20syndrome%2C%26quot%3B%20Li%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20team%20took%20a%20two-pronged%20approach%20to%20keeping%20elevated%20IL-6%20out%20of%20the%20brain%20in%20mice.%20Their%20first%20strategy%20neutralised%20IL-6%20with%20custom%20antibodies.%20The%20second%20used%20CRISPR%20to%20reduce%20the%20levels%20of%20IL-6%20receptors%20in%20AP%20neurons.%20Both%20tactics%20produced%20the%20same%20results%20--%20the%20mice%20started%20eating%20again%2C%20stopped%20losing%20weight%2C%20and%20lived%20longer%2C%20the%20study%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20brain%20is%20so%20powerful%20in%20regulating%20the%20peripheral%20system.%20Simply%20changing%20a%20small%20number%20of%20neurons%20in%20the%20brain%20has%20a%20profound%20effect%20on%20whole-body%20physiology.%20I%20knew%20there%20was%20an%20interaction%20between%20tumours%20and%20brain%20function%2C%20but%20not%20to%20this%20extent%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Li.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720513080000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2020-05%2F6tvmdl64_hospital-generic_625x300_20_May_20.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fmost-cancer-patients-die-of-cachexia-not-cancer-read-details-6063036%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22When%20tumours%20in%20cancer%20patients%20elevate%20levels%20of%20an%20immune%20system%20molecule%20called%20Interleukin-6%20(IL-6)%2C%20it%20can%20cause%20severe%20brain%20dysfunction%2C%20which%20leads%20to%20a%20lethal%20wasting%20disease%20called%20'cachexia'%20in%20about%2050%20to%2080%25%20cancer%20patients%2C%20a%20study%20said%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fmost-cancer-patients-die-of-cachexia-not-cancer-read-details-6063036%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fmost-cancer-patients-die-of-cachexia-not-cancer-read-details-6063036%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fmost-cancer-patients-die-of-cachexia-not-cancer-read-details-6063036%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Toxic%20metals%20found%20in%20tampons%22%2C%22content%